{
  "stem": "23942.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, and the ones that I met, like a boy, I remember he always-- I was afraid of him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They, they actually teased Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were, like, annoying Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The non-Jewish boys-- Like what would they do?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They would annoy us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would either throw-- so, like, snow, where I would be afraid of this boy when I-- when I did see.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was intimidated by them, you know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They intimidated the Jewish girls when they saw us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In other words, if I had to pass by this Jew-- I remember, this non-Jew-- he-- I was afraid of him.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They always, you know, started up with the Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I, I was always avoiding.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they didn't do anything serious.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But nevertheless, it was-- it was annoying to-- because they always started up whether it was Jewish girls or Jewish boys, you know.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So Jewish boys kept with other-- that-- for that reason.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had to-- they had to keep with other Jewish boys because they, they shouldn't be annoyed by the non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You understand what I'm saying?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that's what it was like.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Even though they were neighbors, non-Jew-- but everybody they knew their place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They knew they were non-Jew.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We knew we were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's the way it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "What do you remember as a child from your nice life that you had?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "When do you remember things starting to change, from a child's point of view?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first time I heard bad things in my life was when my mother mentioned that we were going to have to put, like, protection on the glass, like tape, so in case the bombs fall or the gas or something, it shouldn't break and fall.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was the very first time I heard.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
